---

Adjust rack to top position and preheat oven to 425 degrees. In a #medium pot{}, combine @farro{3/4%cup}, @veggie stock concentrate{1}, and 3½ cups water. Bring to a boil and cook until farro is tender, ~{25-30%minutes}. Keep covered off heat until ready to serve.

> If you end up with any excess stock, simply pour it out. Alternatively, if stock evaporates before farro is done, add a splash of water.

Meanwhile, wash and dry all produce. Dice @sweet potato{1} into ½-inch pieces. Toss on a #baking sheet{} with half the @fry seasoning{1%tablespoon} and a large drizzle of @olive oil{}. Season with @salt{} and @pepper{}.

Roast on top rack until golden brown and tender, ~{20-25%minutes}.

While sweet potato roasts, zest and halve @lemon{1}. In a #medium microwave-safe bowl{}, combine juice from lemon and @sugar{1%tsp}; stir until sugar has dissolved. Add @shredded red cabbage{4%ounce} and 2 TBSP water; toss to coat. Microwave for ~{1%minute}. Season with salt and pepper. Set aside, stirring occasionally, until ready to serve.

Mince or grate @garlic{2%cloves}. In a #small bowl{}, combine @mayonnaise{2%tablespoon}, @sour cream{2%tablespoon}, as much lemon zest and garlic as you like, and @harissa powder{1%tablespoon} to taste (start with a small pinch, then taste and add more from there if you like). Add water 1 tsp at a time until mixture reaches a drizzling consistency. Season with salt and pepper.

Remove and discard any large ribs from @kale{4%ounce}. Heat a large drizzle of @olive oil{} in a #large pan{} over medium-high heat. Add kale and season with salt and pepper. Cook, stirring occasionally, until tender, ~{5-7%minutes}. Stir in @butter{1%tablespoon} until melted. Remove pan from heat.

While kale cooks, halve and core @apple{1}; cut half the apple into a small dice. Stir @butter{1%tablespoon} into farro until melted. Stir in diced apple and season with salt and pepper.

Divide farro between #bowls{} and top with kale, pickled cabbage, and sweet potato. Drizzle with dressing. Sprinkle with @pepitas{1/2%ounce} and serve.

> 4 SERVINGS: Use 6 cups water for farro, all the Fry Seasoning, 2 tsp sugar, and 4 TBSP water for pickling. Use 2 TBSP butter for kale and farro. Use whole apple instead of half.